This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with RGB-D semantic segmentation using convolutional neural networks. It also involves the processing of depth data, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of neural networks for image segmentation. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the incorporation of geometric information into CNNs, which is a common problem in AI. 

Robotics (cs.RO) is a possible sub-category as the paper mentions the high computation and memory cost of existing methods, which is a common issue in robotics. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the use of neural networks for image segmentation and introduces new operations for information propagation.
